		<li id="comment-187">
			<div class="comment_author">
				<strong><a href='http://bacteriality.com/about-the-mp/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Amy Proal</a></strong> said, on November 3rd, 2007 at <a href="http://ventedspleen.com/blog/2007/10/22/24-hour-comic-everything-you-never-wanted-to-know-about-crohns-disease/comment-page-3/#comment-187">10:00 pm</a>
			</div>
			
			<p>Hi Tom,</p>
<p>Thanks for making me laugh. Does your bathroom have an easel? : )</p>
<p>Listen, I&#8217;m not sure you&#8217;re familiar with it, but one treatment option for autoimmune diseases&#8211; one which I&#8217;ve used with good success&#8211; is antibiotic-based and called the Marshall Protocol. There are currently patients on it with Crohn&#8217;s, and they&#8217;re doing really well. I believe in it enough to have started a website, Bacteriality.com (see link) where I interview patients, doctors, and researchers about it.</p>
<p>One thing about being ill is you&#8217;re never short of people telling you how to beat it, but I figured I&#8217;d take the risk of annoying you and say you might want to check this treatment out.</p>
<p>Amy</p>

		</li>

	
