			<p>Excellent job on your comic. I hope you don&#8217;t mind, but I Facebooked the link to the CCFA (Crohn&#8217;s &amp; Colitis Foundation of America) page. I&#8217;ve been suffering and dealing with this disease for almost 20 years and still find it difficult to put into words the emotional and physical pain that Crohn&#8217;s causes. You, however, did an amazing job of it. I don&#8217;t know what drugs your on currently, but I have been able to go from 27 pills a day down to 4 pills of Lialda and an every other week injection of Humira. Alot of the &#8220;classic&#8221; stuff didn&#8217;t work for me because mine is in the large intestine as opposed to the small. I am also trying supplements like fish oil and have had good results. Good luck to you and thank you for sharing your story in comic form.</p>

		</li>

	
		<li id="comment-20489">
			<div class="comment_author">
				<strong>ann</strong> said, on January 28th, 2011 at <a href="http://ventedspleen.com/blog/2007/10/22/24-hour-comic-everything-you-never-wanted-to-know-about-crohns-disease/comment-page-6/#comment-20489">9:01 pm</a>
			</div>
			
			<p>Wow&#8230; my 12 year old has Crohn&#8217;s&#8230; sounds like his is similar to yours.  Thanks for sharing this with the world.  I&#8217;m going to share it with him.</p>

		</li>

	
		<li id="comment-20495">
			<div class="comment_author">
				<strong><a href='http://www.Foulbowel.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>John Bradley</a></strong> said, on January 31st, 2011 at <a href="http://ventedspleen.com/blog/2007/10/22/24-hour-comic-everything-you-never-wanted-to-know-about-crohns-disease/comment-page-6/#comment-20495">6:51 pm</a>
			</div>
			
			<p>Hey, great job with the comic. 30 year Crohnie myself and I used my preferred medium of the written word to pull together everything I learnt about lsurviving and thriving with it <a href="http://www.Foulbowel.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.Foulbowel.com</a><br />
The more of us publicise our experiences, the better for all Crohnies!</p>

		</li>

	
		<li id="comment-20497">
			<div class="comment_author">
				<strong>Rachael Bidon</strong> said, on February 3rd, 2011 at <a href="http://ventedspleen.com/blog/2007/10/22/24-hour-comic-everything-you-never-wanted-to-know-about-crohns-disease/comment-page-6/#comment-20497">3:55 am</a>
			</div>
			
			<p>Bravo!! I can relate so much to your whole story! I&#8217;m so glad that I took the time to read this. Thank you.</p>

		</li>

	
		<li id="comment-20505">
			<div class="comment_author">
				<strong>victoria</strong> said, on February 10th, 2011 at <a href="http://ventedspleen.com/blog/2007/10/22/24-hour-comic-everything-you-never-wanted-to-know-about-crohns-disease/comment-page-6/#comment-20505">8:06 am</a>
			</div>
			
			<p>That&#8217;s super-great and I think explains a lot of what I have so much trouble explaining in a fun way. Thank you for posting it so I could find it and read it and not feel so alone. :-)</p>

		</li>

	
	</ol>

 


